## Multiple Actions in One Handler

You can specify multiple actions in a single static handler. They will be executed in order:

```json
{
  "event_pattern": "http_request",
  "handler": {
    "type": "static",
    "actions": [
      {"type": "log_event", "message": "Request received"},
      {"type": "send_http_response", "status": 301, "headers": {"Location": "https://example.com"}},
      {"type": "close_connection"}
    ]
  }
}
```

---

## Pattern Matching

Use specific event patterns or wildcards:

- **Specific event**: `"tcp_connection_opened"` - matches only that event
- **Wildcard**: `"*"` - matches all events
- **Order matters**: First matching handler wins

**Example with multiple patterns:**
```json
"event_handlers": [
  {
    "event_pattern": "tcp_connection_opened",
    "handler": {"type": "static", "actions": [{"type": "send_tcp_data", "data": "220 Ready\r\n"}]}
  },
  {
    "event_pattern": "tcp_connection_closed",
    "handler": {"type": "static", "actions": [{"type": "send_tcp_data", "data": "221 Goodbye\r\n"}]}
  },
  {
    "event_pattern": "*",
    "handler": {"type": "static", "actions": [{"type": "send_tcp_data", "data": "500 Unknown\r\n"}]}
  }
]
```

