## Advanced: Fallback to LLM

If your script encounters a situation it can't handle deterministically, it can return `{"fallback_to_llm": true}` to delegate to the LLM:

```python
import json, sys
data = json.load(sys.stdin)
command = data['event']['command']

# Handle simple commands with script
if command == 'HELP':
    print(json.dumps({'actions': [{'type': 'send_tcp_data', 'data': 'Commands: HELP, QUIT\n'}]}))
elif command == 'QUIT':
    print(json.dumps({'actions': [{'type': 'close_connection'}]}))
else:
    # Complex command - let LLM handle it
    print(json.dumps({'fallback_to_llm': true}))
```

